SIMPLE: graining
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Graining
<hw>Grain"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Indentation;
roughening; milling, as on edges of coins.</def>
<rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A process in dressing leather, by which the skin is
softened and the grain raised.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Painting or staining, in imitation of the grain of
wood, stone, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Soap Making)</fld> <def>The process of separating
soap from spent lye, as with salt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Graining</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Graining
<hw>Grain"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small
European fresh-water fish (<spn>Leuciscus vulgaris</spn>); -- called
also <altname>dobule</altname>, and <altname>dace</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grains</ent>⟦br⟧
